Hi everyone! I have a super simple question, and I feel like I have done this a ton, but I can not get this to work. I am working on a theme and I am trying to detect if they are including jquery in the settings area of the portal using this simple hubl, but it is firing regardless. Do I have something wrong here:
```{% if not site_settings.include_jquery  %}
  &lt;script src="<https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js>"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; 
{% endif %}```

Try this:
    {% if not site_settings.include_jquery %}
      {{ require_js("<https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.4.1.js>", "footer") }}
    {% endif %}
